      <hedline>
        <hl1>Boys Charged With Abuse</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Five 12- and 13-year-old boys are arrested and suspended from junior high school in Rockaway Park, Queens, after 12-year-old girl accuses them of sexually abusing her outside school building (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Five 12- and 13-year-old boys were arrested and suspended from a junior high school in Queens after a 12-year-old girl accused them of sexually abusing her outside the school building, the authorities said yesterday.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Five 12- and 13-year-old boys were arrested and suspended from a junior high school in Queens after a 12-year-old girl accused them of sexually abusing her outside the school building, the authorities said yesterday.</p>
        <p>The attack took place at 9:45 a.m. Monday at Junior High School 180 on Beach 104th Street in Rockaway Park, said Detective Edward Reuss, a Police Department spokesman. All the boys were charged with sexual abuse and the case will be handled in Family Court. No details on the charges were available last night.</p>
      </block>
